{{Top|leg}}
'''Messaging centers''' were devices that could be used by would-be visitors and solicitors to record and store videonotes for the residents of a household in the event that the residents were unable or unwilling to answer the door. Using an [[infopanel]] on the other side of the door, the resident could then play the messages that had been left by the visitors.

